# README Formatting Preferences

When creating or editing README.md files, follow these formatting guidelines:

## Section Headers
- All section headers must include relevant emojis that match the section content
- Use appropriate heading levels (# for main title, ## for sections, ### for subsections)

## Tone and Style
- Maintain a friendly and concise tone throughout
- Be welcoming and approachable
- Keep explanations clear and to the point
- Avoid overly technical jargon unless necessary

## Lists and Organization
- Use bullet lists for features, requirements, and setup steps
- Prefer `-` for unordered lists
- Use numbered lists only for sequential steps
- Keep list items concise (1-2 lines maximum)

## Code Blocks
- Include at least one code block per README
- Use appropriate language tags for syntax highlighting (```bash, ```python, ```javascript, etc.)
- Provide clear context before each code block
- Include installation commands, usage examples, or configuration snippets

